description:
&lt;p&gt;Surrey Heartlands CCG is seeking a Primary Care Administrator who will provide both administrative and project support to members of the Primary Care Team across Surrey Heartlands. This is a critical supporting role, which will enable the efficient functioning of the wider team. The post holder will be motivated and enthusiastic, with a keen eye for attention to detail, as well as a proactive approach. The post-holder will play a key role in providing administrative and project support, including organisation of meetings and events, and the preparation and production of agendas and minutes. The post-holder will be the main contact person for queries from GP practices, and as such will need to have strong inter-personal skills and be confident in developing relationships with a wide range of stakeholders.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Microsoft Word, Excel and Outlook experience is essential. Experience of working in the NHS is preferable but not essential. This is a fast paced work environment and we are looking for an Administrator who thrives from this. Some travel may be required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We would warmly welcome any questions about this opportunity - please contact Emily Taylor (details on the right), in the first instance.&lt;/p&gt;
